data.current_description: Start manual transfer runs to be executed now with schedule_time equal to current time. The transfer runs can be created for a time range where the run_time is between start_time (inclusive) and end_time (exclusive), or for a specific run_time.
data.description_suggestion: Manually triggers one or more transfer runs for a specified transfer configuration to execute immediately. Supports two modes: (1) create a single run with current timestamp, or (2) create multiple runs for a time range [start_time, end_time) where start_time is inclusive and end_time is exclusive. All times are in UTC. Returns information about the created transfer runs. Use this to backfill data or force immediate execution outside the regular schedule.
